{
  "texts": [
    "Overall, the findings suggest a promising outlook for the future of CSL for medical data but also underscore the need for continued validation and rigorous evaluation of the developed techniques.",
    "The selected studies were evaluated using three empirical methods: Case Study (CS), Historical-Based evaluation (HBE), and survey.",
    "Figure 4 illustrates the distribution of research and empirical types.",
    "It can be observed from the bubble plot that HBE was the most prevalent empirical type, with 117 papers (65.4%) using publicly available medical datasets to assess their models.",
    "Of these papers, the majority (105) proposed and evaluated novel or improved solutions, 11 studies evaluated existing ones, and only one study was dedicated to reviewing and evaluating previously suggested methods."
  ]
}